choices.rubric: (no value)

Recognizes how the nurse- patient/family relationship impacts the patient experience. Introduces self as a Registered Nurse and describes role.
Consistently wears identification. Establishes open communication.

choices.name: Expert
choices.rubric: ***Challenges and adapts systems to maximize the benefits for patient care.

Initiates referrals.

choices.name: Fully Competent

Initiates, recognizes and values professional collaborative communication and the positive effect on patient outcomes. Identifies and utilizes collaborative resources.

Frequently initiates consults with health care team.

Acts as resource to nursing and health care team.

choices.name: Expert

Through shared values and a clear professional identify, demonstrates and role models an interdisciplinary collaborative approach to patient care.
Participates and/or leads team care conference.

Takes responsibility for developing beginning team relationships.
Seeks assistance with resolving conflict. Meets professional commitments consistently.
Asks for and accepts help when needed.

choices.name: Fully Competent
choices.rubric:
Functions as an independent and supportive team member. Provides assistance to others. Demonstrates empathy and compassion in interactions with team members.
Approaches conflict situations in a constructive manner.

choices.name: Proficient
choices.rubric:
Fosters mutual regard, respect, and trust.
Demonstrates flexibility.
Creates conditions and relationships that promote creative, innovative, and positive processes and outcomes.
Role models behaviors that demonstrate compassion and caring.
Fosters otherÂ’s development of conflict resolution skills.
Demonstrates active engagement to enhance patient care and promote a positive workplace.

choices.name: Expert
choices.rubric:
Demonstrates team values that orient people to care about performance and success of others.
Recognizes value of conflict in individual and organization learning and growth.

questionGroups.summary: Committed to the professional development of self and others.

questions.name: Self

choices.name: (not set)
choices.rubric: (no value)

choices.name: Advanced Beginner
choices.rubric:
Engages in self assessment related to orientation and ongoing learning needs and seeks out unit resources to assist in meeting needs.
Completes mandatory/ competency requirements during orientation and annually.

choices.name: Fully Competent
choices.rubric:
Sets goals for knowledge/ skill enhancement within the practice setting.
Seeks out additional learning experiences within practice area: Â• Unit specific certifications Â• Consultation with experts Â• Inservices/rounds Â• Collaborates with multidisciplinary team

choices.name: Proficient
choices.rubric:
***Sets goals for knowledge/skill enhancement within and beyond the practice setting.
***Attends inservice(s)/CE within and beyond practice area.

choices.name: Expert
choices.rubric:
***Sets goals in self directed manner and actively seeks out opportunities for knowledge/skill enhancement within and beyond the practice setting.
***Evidence of advancing professional identify (at least one): Â• Certification in specialty (ACCN, ANCC Specialty Areas) Â• Active participation in Professional organization (i.e., clinical specialty organizations, UMPNC, MNA, ANA, UAN) Â• Active membership/ leadership role in institutional groups related to nursing

questionGroups.summary: Demonstrates ongoing innovation byreviewing, critiquing and applying existing evidence to practice. Continually improves practice by applying performance improvement methodologies.

choices.name: Proficient

choices.name: Expert
choices.rubric:

Evaluates effectiveness of innovation/practice challenges.

choices.name: Proficient
choices.rubric:
***Participates in unit/area based/institutional Continuous Quality Improvement projects.
Presents at unit based educational forums.

choices.name: Expert

Implements change in practice for a population of patients based on the application of current research findings and evaluates effectiveness of practice changes.
